				<div class="SIT"><br><ul><li>Four nucleoid-like proteins in enteric bacteria , H-NS , StpA , Hha , and YdgT have a predilection for binding to A+T rich sequences and repress transcription of SPI-2 genes ( rev. in [ 14 ] ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19229334" target="_blank">19229334</a>]<br></li>
